THE LIAR AND THE LOCK
GM Reference Block - Orion, Nora, and the Carrion Mentor
"He is courting the kill-switch. He may even know it."

Companion to Players/orion 2, Npcs/Nora the haunted, and The Sentient
Sword. SUPERSEDES: orion 2 Section VI "The Song of Severance" (the
Severance is no longer a composed song -- see Section III); refines
Nora doc Section X (the dark trajectory gains a second branch).
Nora is the hub of this doc: three arcs meet in her.

HARD FACT: Nora is 18 (canon note in her doc; the accident was at age
6, twelve years carrying the gems). All older "14" references are
superseded. Orion's player intends romance; the relationship is to be
played genuine on both sides -- the danger is the world around it,
never a question of his sincerity.

=====================================================================
I. THE COURTSHIP INSIDE A SURVEILLANCE STATE
=====================================================================
The Ring of the Pale Regent sees what Orion sees and hears what he
hears. THE ROMANCE CANNOT BE PRIVATE. Valerius is in the room for all
of it, from the first fumbled kindness on.

VALERIUS'S RESPONSE: approval. Love walking toward his asset is
  leverage arriving free of charge. He gives no order and makes no
  comment -- until, weeks in, one whisper mentions her name in
  passing and moves on. Nothing else. The leash-tug that says I see
  what you treasure. From that whisper forward, every contract has a
  hostage in it that no one has taken yet. Do not use her again for
  a long time. The silence after the name is the pressure.

THE ROMANCE AS BLIND SPOT: Orion knows the Ring has gaps. Hours spent
  with Nora are perfect cover for Severance work -- courtship and
  conspiracy in the same sessions, indistinguishable to the watcher.
  The relationship is sincere AND operationally useful, and Orion
  never has to choose which -- until someone makes him.

HOW NORA LEARNS ABOUT THE RING: she deduces it. She is learning tonal
  diagnostics from him; stage a quiet lesson where she hears a
  frequency in his hand that he did not play. The girl who cannot lie
  discovering her teacher's permanent listener is the romance's first
  real test. GM: hand her the anomaly; let the players drive what she
  does with it. If they never give her a lesson close enough to hear
  it, she stays ignorant -- and the cover she provides stays unwitting,
  which is its own kind of awful.

THE ASYMMETRY (the engine): Orion is a professional liar carrying
  three truths that would each end this -- the Argonian woman in the
  Warrens, the fangs he showed Mila, and Saijah held in reserve as
  leverage against Varon. Nora is incapable of lying and trusts
  honesty above all currencies. He decides, every session, which
  truth she gets. Track the three. Each one is a loaded scene waiting
  for a trigger, and the Mila truth is the one Bjorn already knows.

=====================================================================
II. NORA IS THE KILL-SWITCH (conditional canon)
=====================================================================
Her trauma response unbinds Daedric workings and shatters enchanted
items. The party contains two members whose existences ARE Daedric-
bound artifacts: Orion (vampirism and the Ring) and Alfonso (a
corroded enchanted rapier -- the exact category her panic deletes).
The campaign's two monsters orbit an anxious eighteen-year-old whose
terror can permanently kill either of them by accident. She would
never recover from doing it.

CONDITIONAL -- THE DEDUCTION IS EARNED, NEVER AUTOMATIC: no one knows
this yet, including her. Alfonso deduces it ONLY if play shows him
the evidence -- he witnesses (or hears a firsthand account of) a
trauma response that unmakes an enchantment, or he studies her
closely during distress near Daedric work. If the condition lands,
his response is in-character chilling: he does not withdraw from his
most promising student. He starts teaching her CONTROL, patiently,
thoroughly, with a very personal motivation he never states. Orion
can reach the same deduction by the same standard of evidence. If
the table never produces the evidence, the gun stays in the drawer
-- loaded, unnoticed, true.

=====================================================================
III. THE SONG OF SEVERANCE, REDESIGNED (supersedes orion 2 VI)
=====================================================================
The Severance cannot be composed. It can only be TRANSCRIBED.

The frequency that breaks a Daedric binding without taking the hand
off is the one Nora's soul produces involuntarily in her unbinding
response. Orion's research arc is no longer "develop a song" -- it is
capture, understand, and reproduce what she does in her worst
moments. Requirements stand from orion 2 (study with Nora, Dwemer
data, GEAR as an indiscreet oracle); the one-shot rule stands
(a failed attempt alerts Valerius). What changes is the moral floor:
  - The material of his freedom is her pain.
  - She would give it willingly -- if asked. ASKING is the hard part
    for a man whose architecture is never revealing what he needs.
  - The Type 4 question of the romance: does he ever ENGINEER a
    trauma response to get a cleaner recording? That is the moment
    instrumental Orion and sincere Orion can no longer both exist.
    Never force it; leave the temptation on the table where his
    player can see it.
GM: GEAR can identify the frequency-class from a description ("a
soul-sourced counter-resonance; the Dwemer called these unweaving
tones") with complete, indiscriminate honesty, in front of anyone.

=====================================================================
IV. THE CARRION MENTOR -- ALFONSO'S LANE
=====================================================================
THE FALSE PROOF (already canon, next-session doc): Alfonso choosing
to persist as a willed soul in a blade confirms, falsely, that her
parents are "still in there," intact and recoverable.

THE PROJECTION BLUEPRINT (new): the Sentient Sword canon hands her
more than confirmation. Alfonso demonstrates that a soul in a vessel
GROWS ITS OWN BODY around the anchor. Her plan grows a second branch:

  BRANCH 1 (original): extract the souls, implant into Davinia's
    substrate-converted body. Unchanged; see Nora doc Section X.
  BRANCH 2 (new): seat each parent in a phylactery and let them
    project themselves back. Cleaner. Kinder. Requires violating no
    one. And FALSE HOPE -- Alfonso's projection runs on a Daedric
    synthesis and a god's favor; her parents are ordinary souls,
    Soul Cairn-bound, in gems whose contents she has never verified.
    The horror of Branch 2 is that it looks like the ethical option,
    so pursuing it feels like virtue.

THE SHARED PRIZE: the missing binding technique lives in exactly one
place -- the Afflicted Conclave's soul-vessel scripture in WINDHELM.
Alfonso's phylactery cure-lead and Nora's textbook are the same
document. If the party takes Fire A, two of them want that archive
for two different resurrections, and only one is honest about it.

WHO DISCOVERS HER PLAN FIRST -- PLAY-DRIVEN. Do not schedule it.
Whoever gets close enough first, gets there first:
  THE ALFONSO ROUTE (discovery = acceleration): he has been inside
    her reasoning for weeks and reads research the way Maven reads
    ledgers. His response is not alarm -- it is PEER REVIEW. Clinical
    refinement of the vessel plan, because in his worldview she is
    correct. His approval becomes the dark path's engine.
  THE ORION ROUTE (discovery = the fulcrum): inside her research,
    inside her trust, Diagnostic Song in hand. His three masters give
    three answers -- the Brotherhood does not care, Valerius would
    WANT the technique, the usurper sees that her vessel-craft and
    his ring-breaking are one discipline. The only voice that says
    stop her is whatever the romance has grown in him. Her crossroads
    becomes his.
  BOTH ROUTES CAN FIRE in either order; the second discovery happens
    in a changed landscape the first one made.

THE CONVERGENCE SCENE (stage when the table gives an opening): Nora,
alone on a watch, playing the Diagnostic Song at the dormant rapier --
both apprenticeships aimed at one object; research method, dark plan,
and a violation of a sleeping friend in a single quiet image.
  WHAT SHE HEARS (canon): two signatures where there should be one.
  The soul in the iron -- and, braided through it, the Namira-resonance
  of the unworn Crown pooling nearby. She has no frame for the second
  signature. She learns something TRUE and misreads it: two presences
  in one vessel = "two souls can share an anchor" = both branches of
  her plan just got, in her mind, experimental support. If she ever
  tells Alfonso what she heard, he learns the Crown is doing
  something to his phylactery that no one knew. (What it is doing is
  GM ammunition for his arc -- design when needed, no commitment now.)

THE PATRON RESONANCE (structural, never stated): Namira courts
Alfonso OUT of form while Nora studies him to put souls back INTO
form. If he chooses the deeper void at his crossroads, he tells her
-- without intending to -- that vessels do not matter. The mentor's
apotheosis is the apprentice's refutation. Leave it for the table to
find; do not force the connection (Rule 4).

