V. CROSSING THREADS
=====================================================================
- CONSTANCE [PENDING finale]: if Orion executes Valerius's
  enthrallment, he field-tests magical loyalty-binding of an
  unwilling mind fifty feet from Nora -- the exact ethics of her own
  plan, performed by the man she is falling for. Place the fuse
  deliberately: does she ever learn, and from whom?
- SAIJAH HOLDS THE EXIT: Nora's light path (the root network reaching
  into the Soul Cairn) arrives only through Saijah -- who is the pawn
  in Orion's leverage scheme. If Saijah ever learns she was used, the
  blast radius includes Nora's one alternative to the dark plan.
  Orion's sins are load-bearing in Nora's salvation.
- CARRYING THE SWORD: Nora volunteers for the rapier (Sentient Sword
  Section III says she should not be allowed to). Every hour she
  carries him is mentor-exposure, false-proof reinforcement, and --
  if he is Wakeful -- conversation no one else hears. The party
  deciding who carries Alfonso is also deciding Nora's dosage.
- VARON: the handler watches Orion's sloppiness AND his new soft
  spot. A handler who has his own unsanctioned attachment (Saijah)
  recognizing Orion's is leverage flowing BOTH ways for the first
  time.
- MILA: Bjorn knows what Orion did to her. The Vow stands. If the
  Mila truth reaches Nora, it arrives with Bjorn's fury attached.

=====================================================================
VI. GM NOTES & PACING
=====================================================================
- The romance is genuine. Both of them. Play Nora's side with the
  hesitancy of someone who has never been chosen before by someone
  who SAW her power and stayed. The tragedy potential comes from the
  world (the Ring, the secrets, the plan), never from revealing the
  love itself was a con.
- Track the three truths (Argonian / Mila / Saijah-leverage) like
  clocks. Each surfaced truth re-prices the others.
- The Severance is a multi-session arc with one shot at the end. Its
  stations: Nora deduces the Ring -> she joins knowingly -> the
  frequency is identified as hers -> the recording problem -> the
  asking problem -> the attempt. Let stations move or merge with
  play; never skip the asking problem.
- Valerius says her name ONCE. Resist every urge to repeat it.
- The dark plan's discovery order is the players' to determine by
  where they put their attention. Prep both routes; run the one the
  table earns.
- Nora remains sympathetic at every stage (her doc's standing rule).
  The romance must make her MORE sympathetic and the plan MORE
  understandable -- love teaching her, for the first time since age
  six, that recovering the dead might not be the only future. That
  hope is the light path's real foothold, whatever Saijah supplies.
